# ESLint Config Project

Shared ESLint configuration for **Creo** projects. Consumed by vecta, photos, creo, and others. Flat config; TypeScript ESLint, Prettier, JSDoc, stylistic, import, perfectionist; async correctness, complexity, no-magic-numbers, no-console. Exports default and `createConfig(options)`; no project-structure plugin.

## Required Reading

- `CLAUDE.md` — comprehensive project instructions
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` — setup, commands, release
- `AGENTS.md` — agent quick reference
- `docs/ESLINT-STANDARDS.md` — rule philosophy and severity policy
- `docs/AI-CODE-STANDARDS.md` — AI code patterns

## Key Resources

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `rules.js` | Rule groups (commonjsPreventRules, prettier, jsDoc, stylisticTs, tsEslint); merged `rules` export |
| `utils.js` | `getTsConfigFile()`, `debug()`; Node globals via config |
| `eslint.config.js` | Exports default and `createConfig`; flat config; plugins, languageOptions, rules |
| `constants.js` | Severity levels, naming convention presets |
| `docs/` | ESLINT-AUDIT, ESLINT-STANDARDS, AI-CODE-STANDARDS |

## Architecture

- **rules.js** — Constants and rule objects; no magic values. Exports `rules`, `jsDoc`, `prettier`, etc.
- **utils.js** — Config resolution and debug logging; used by eslint.config.js at load time.
- **eslint.config.js** — `createConfig({ ignores?, tsconfig? })`; single flat config; ignores, recommended configs, file overrides, plugins, settings.
- **test/** — Vitest (utils, ESLint fixture); `*.test.mjs`.

## Prettier/@stylistic Boundary

Prettier handles ALL formatting via `prettier/prettier: error`. The `@stylistic/*` plugin is only used for blank-line structure rules (lines-around-comment, lines-between-class-members). Never add `@stylistic/*` formatting rules.

## Verification

Before submitting: `npm test && npm run build`.
